                                                                                    /* Specification: This is used as a specification for our TLA+ model. It assumes all variables are hidden (v) but not philosophically correct so we don't worry about this in the end .*/      // The variable 'XInit', and its successor, will be represented by XAct(i , xInit –> vNext). This is used to represent an A_0 action or a stay at current position for actions performed on V due to being changed from one state of value. */
                                                                                    /* Next: The next-state relation which represents the transition after each event (A_1 -> 2xInit/v, xNext).*/      // XAct Operator : This operator is used as a successor or resultant in an A_0 action when v changes from 0 to another value. It assumes that if i=1 then it means we are performing the next state of V due to being changed by An Action (A_i -> 2xInit/v, xNext). */
                                                                                    /* Specification: This is used as a specification for our TLA+ model and also represents all hidden variables v.*/      // The variable 'XAct' will represent the part of system that has been changed by A_0 or /and A_1 actions . For example, if x changes from 2xInit to an new value then it means we are performing a change on X due to being affected by Action (Ai -> 2xNext/v). */
                                                                                    /* Next: The next-state relation which represents the transition after each event.*/      // This is used as representation of A_1 action or stay at current position for actions performed when v changes from 0 and another value respectively .   For example, if x change to a new state then it means we are performing an Action (Ai -> 2xNext/v). */
